The pattern to match would be `[[<filename>]]` where `<filename>` is the name of the image file, typically ending with an image file extension such as `.jpeg`, `.jpg`, `.png`, etc.

In the provided input text, we can see two instances of such patterns:

- `[[yh.jpeg]]`
- `[[zh.jpeg]]`

The extracted image filenames, separated by a newline (`\n`), would be:

```

```
